xusb_l.h File Reference

Detailed Description

This header file contains identifiers and low-level driver function prototypes (or macros) that can be used to access the USB device. High-level driver function prototypes are defined in xusb.h.

 1.00a hvm  2/22/07  First release
 2.00a hvm  12/2/08  Updated the register offset values as per the new USB

 4.04a bss  10/22/13 Added macros for HSIC PHY registers.

Status Register and Interrupt Enable Register


 Status Register 

This register holds the status flags for the USB device.

 Interrupt Enable Register 

This register is used to enable interrupt sources for the USB device. Writing a '1' to a bit in this register enables the corresponding Interrupt. Writing a '0' to a bit in this register disables the corresponding Interrupt.

Both these registers have the same bit definitions and are only defined once.

          #define XUsb_WriteReg          
          ( 
          BaseAddress,         

          
          
          RegOffset,         

          
          
          RegisterValue 
                    
           ) 
             XUsb_Out32((BaseAddress) + (RegOffset), (RegisterValue))
        

      

    		
  





  

    
       
    
    



Write to the specified USB device register.


Parameters:

  

    
BaseAddress contains the base address of the device. 

    
RegOffset contains the offset from the 1st register of the device to select the specific register. 

    
RegisterValue is the value to be written to the register.

  




Returns:
None.


Note:
C-Style signature: void XUsb_WriteReg(u32 BaseAddress, u32 RegOffset, u32 RegisterValue);
